(100226, 'Lionel ', 'ARTUSIO', 'Mr', '', '30', 'ch', '', '', 'lionel@dybaw.com', 'Fondation pour l\'Innovation et la Coopération Suisse', 'Lionel brings over 10 years of progressive experience in founding, funding, and managing global FinTech businesses in Europe (UK, Ireland, Monaco, France). His most recent entrepreneurial experiences include a CEO position for an European micro-payment platform based in the UK & Ireland. \r\n\r\nLionel joined the investor side of the market with several positions as Head of Investments for Goldman-Sachs (with to tier investments such as Circle, BlueFin Payments) and VP for BlackFin Capital Fund. Acting as an Alternative Fund Investment Manager in Switzerland (Tech & Impact investing in the Health-Tech, Ag-tech and Fintech sector):\r\n\r\n- Impact Investing Fund Advisor (PE, SFO/MFO, HNWIs): Managed 46 Impact Projects.\r\n- Blockchain & Security token boutique advisory;\r\n- Venture Capital Managing Director: Tech4Good; Impact investing.', 22, 2, 1, 1),
(100227, ' Edem ', 'ADJAMAGBO', 'Mr', '', '3', 'tg', '', '', 'edem.adjamagbo@semoa-group.com', 'Semoa Group ', 'Edem ADJAMAGBO ingénieur en Business Intelligence, fondateur de la startup Semoa\r\nTogo.\r\nEdem grandi au Togo à lomé, il a rejoint Nantes, sa ville d\'adoption pour son cycle\r\ningénieur. Après avoir travaillé trois ans pour des sociétés de services en France il s\'est\r\nlancé dans l\'aventure entrepreneuriale avec la fervante idée de devenir le Paypal de\r\nl\'Afrique d\'ici à cinq ans.\r\n\r\nLa startup qu\'il a fondé à pour mission d\'apporter une solution au développement du e-\r\ncommerce ne Afrique à travers le service CashPay', 8, 2, 1, 1),
(100228, 'Toby ', 'SHAPSHAK', 'Mr', '', '119', 'za', '', '', 'toby@mavenmedia.co.za', ' Stuff - Forbes ', 'Toby Shapshak is editor-in-chief and publisher of Stuff, a Forbes contributor and a Financial Mail columnist. He has been writing about technology and the internet for 20 years and his TED Global talk on innovation in Africa has nearly 1,5-million views (and has nearly as many views as Richard Branson). He has written about Africa\'s tech and start-up ecosystem for Forbes, CNN and The Guardian in London. He was named in GQ\'s top 30 men in media and the Mail & Guardian newspaper\'s influential young South Africans. He has been featured in the New York Times. GQ said he \"has become the most high-profile technology journalist in the country\". \r\n', 31, 2, 1, 1),
(100229, 'Jawher', 'FERJAOUI', 'Mr', '', '3', 'tn', '', '', 'jawher.ferjaoui@tunisia.gov.tn ', 'La Poste', '- 20 years of experience in the use of ICT as a strategic lever to create value, to build new process and to facilitate management with better efficiency , with good capacity to adapt and innovate...\r\n- Design innovative digital strategies\r\n- High ability, to build, to lead and to drive complex Projects.\r\n- Results-based budgeting (RBB)\r\n- Implicated as a source of innovation and transformation applied in several sectors such as ICT, Digital Economy, Health, Social Affairs, business facilities and Transport,\r\n- Specialist in Urbanization of Information Systems \r\n- Good communication skills, flexible and team player with high capability to establish good relationship with all level of management.', 8, 2, 1, 1),
