(100231, 'Ismael ', 'CHERIF', 'Mr', '', '113', 'fr', '', '', 'kx.ismael@gmail.com', '', 'smael KX est un consultant IT indépendant, un agiliste convaincu et un évangéliste de la Blockchain.\r\n\r\nJ\'aide les entreprises sur l\'organisation et le pilotage de leurs projets, mais aussi sur l\'amélioration de l\'organisation des équipes en prêchant l\'agilité et les serious games et en formant les équipes ainsi que les décideurs.\r\n\r\nJe conduis aussi des études et des projets basés sur la technologie blockchain. En effet, le train est en marche et les entreprises qui refusent d\'embarquer maintenant commettent certainement la même erreur que KODAK il y a + de 20 ans', 32, 2, 1, 1),
(100232, 'Karim', 'AHRES', 'Mr', '', '3', 'tn', '', '', 'karim.ahres@satec.com.tn', 'Netcom Tunisia', 'Executive M.B.A Founder of the first ICT Network company in Tunisia Intensive experience in negociation and leadership Good Business , Technical and Managerial Balance Intensive experience in project management Hand-on experience in Human Ressources Multilingual : French , English and Arabic.', 8, 2, 1, 1),
(100233, 'Baidy ', 'SY', 'Mr', '', '110', 'sn', '', '', 'baidy@saytu.co', 'SAYTU SA', 'Diplômé de l’Université Paris Dauphine, Baïdy SYa acquis plusieurs années d’expériences professionnelles internationales (Afrique & France) dans le domaine du management des systèmes d’information et de la cybersécurité. M. SY est rédacteur de plusieurs d’articles etblogger dans le domaine. Il a animé plusieurs conférences internationales et dispense, également, des cours sur le sujet au Centre Africain d’Études Supérieures en Gestion (CESAG) depuis 2014.\r\nFondateur et Directeur Général de SAYTU SA, un cabinet spécialisé dans la cybersécurité et la confiance numérique couvrant l’Afrique Subsaharienne, Baidy SY est également auteur du livre \"En route vers l\'émergence, le Sénégal face au défi de la cybersécurité\"  qui a été nominé au Prix du Livre au Forum International de la Cybersécurité 2018.\r\n\r\n', 8, 2, 1, 1),
(100234, 'Donatien ', 'KOUADIO', 'Mr', '', '30', 'ci', '', '', 'donatienk@gmail.com', 'Mazars ', 'Ingénieur MIAGE de formation, Donatien a exercé en tant que chef de projet dans la plus grande SSII de son pays la côte d’ivoire (SNDI)  avant de rejoindre le groupe bancaire NSIA et ensuite le groupe Bank Of Africa ou il a monté l’activité Audit des SI au sein de l’inspection générale du groupe. Après son passage dans le milieu bancaire, Donatien est au aujourd’hui en charge du département IT Consulting, au sein du cabinet  Mazars CI et couvre 5 pays de la zone UEMOA. (Membre du jury du Abidjan Startup week-end 2015) ', 33, 2, 1, 1),
(100235, 'Sylvere ', 'BOUSSAMBA', 'Mr', '', '110', 'ga', '', '', 'boussambas@gmail.com', 'Ogooue Labs', 'Digital Evangelist, Innovator, Speaker, Coach, Serial Entrepreneur, Teacher, Independent Leadership Trainer at John Maxwell Team, Business mentor for TEEP, Founder of Ogooue Labs (Innovation Lab, Accelerator, Entrepreneurship and Leardership School) in Gabon and DRC, Creative thinker, Hardworker passioned about Africa Economic growth and Development through internet and mobile money.\r\n\r\nA big passion for Connected Applications, Digital Content, Mashed up Applications, Connected Things (IOT), Digital Entrepeneurship, Social Entrepreneurship, Experience & Knowlegde Economy, Traditional and Digital Marketing, Tech Hubs, Incubators, Startups, Leadership, Education, products and customers development. \r\n\r\nIT specialist during 20 years, with competences on IT Service Management (ITIL Certified), Business Intelligence, Business Activity Monitoring and Project Management.\r\n\r\nMember of Entrepr\'OnAir, a community promoting Digital entrepreneurship in DRC through coaching and mentoring. Advisor and Business Angel for LLAB in DRC.', 25, 2, 1, 1),
(100236, 'Samia', 'CHELBI', 'Mme', '', '3', 'tn', '', '', 'samia@3dnetinfo.com', 'NET-INFO School Of Art & technology', 'Samia Chelbi is a university teacher  who has more than 25 years of experience in different fields which are tightly linked to creative technologies.\r\nThe co-founder of the first school of 3D, animation and video Game in North Africa for more than a decade as she contribueted forward in the progress of this industry in Tunisia and Africa.\r\nHer Passion for this realm pushed her into the community work, as she founded in 2004 the Tunisian Association of Creative Technologies (CREATEC).\r\nThis double vocation, social and professional, gave her the means to contribute to the shaping of the ecosystem in collaboration with the public and private actors.\r\nCurrently, she is leading the DigiArtLivingLab project which is the first living lab in North Africa specialized in Digital Arts and certified by ENoLL( European Network of Living Lab) .\r\n', 34, 2, 1, 1),
(100237, 'Serge ', 'DIMITRI PITROIPA', 'Mr', '', '3', 'bf', '', '', 'pitserge9@gmail.com', 'PIT-PRODUCTION', '', 8, 2, 1, 1),
(100238, 'Sénamé ', 'KOFFI AGBODJINOU', 'Mr', '', '110', 'tg', '', '', 'sename@lafricainedarchitecture.com', 'Catalyst', 'Sénamé Koffi AGBODJINOU , fondateur, catalyst L’Africaine d’architecture & WoeLab\r\nArchitecte et anthropologue, Sénamé Koffi Agbodjinou est le créateur de la plateforme de recherche collaborative sur les questions de l’architecture et de la ville africaines ‘L’Africaine d’architecture’. Fondateur de WoeLab, réseau de tech-hubs grassroots togolais dont l’ambition est de “rendre tout le monde égal en face de la technologie” et au sein duquel il a contribué à lancer la demi-douzaine d’entreprises partagées du Groupe #Siliconvillage. Sename est élu depuis 2017 au prestigieux programme fellowship pour entrepreneurs sociaux de la fondation Ashoka.\r\n', 25, 2, 1, 1),
(100241, 'Anis ', 'KALLEL', 'Mr', '', '110', 'tn', '', '99 142 989', 'aniiskallel@gmail.com', 'Kaoun ', 'Born and raised in Tunisia, North Africa, I left to the U.S for college at the age of 19. I attended the University of Rochester on a full scholarship, and studied Computer Science and Business. During these 4 years, I had the opportunity to do research on Human Computer Interaction, and intern at Electronic Arts (E.A) and Microsoft.\r\n\r\nHaving developed an interest and a passion for emerging markets, I took a job with the Swiss investment group Seedstars as their associate for Africa. There, I got the opportunity to travel to 16 African countries to identify the best and most investable early stage startups, and worked with corporates, governments, and startups on growing the entrepreneurship ecosystems, sharing success stories and opportunities, and attracting further investment in the region. \r\n\r\nThis tour furthered my belief that Tunisia has a lot more to offer to the world, and encouraged me to move back home in 2018 as the Co-Founder of a FinTech company called Kaoun - كون (Universe, in Arabic) working on Payments and Credit.', 15, 2, 1, 1),
(100242, 'Jean Yves', 'BASSANGNA ', 'Mr', '', '30', 'cm', '', '', 'bassangna@kiroogames.com', 'Kiro\'o Games', 'Je suis un jeune Camerounais agé de 33 ans, diplômé en sciences économique et de gestion à l’université de Yaoundé II, au Cameroun.\r\nJ’ai arrêté mes études en 2010 pour m’engager d’abord comme employé, puis j’ai monté mon entreprise au côté de MADIBA Guillaume Olivier en 2013 à savoir Kiro’o Games. Je suis un passionné de musique et de système cohérent, auteur compositeur de la bande originale ainsi que la bande sonore du jeu « Aurion : l’Héritage des Kori-Odan », doubleur officiel du héro du jeu à savoir Enzo Kori-Odan.', 15, 2, 1, 1),
(100243, 'Nicolas', 'HOUNTO', 'Mr', '', '110', 'bj', '', '', 'nhounto@yahoo.fr', 'Africangels', 'Nicolas Hounto est Ingénieur diplômé de l’ESIEA (Informatique Électronique-Automatique) et\r\ntitulaire d’un Master en management général de l’ESSEC. Il est également Master Coach de l’ICI\r\nCoach (Franco-suisse).\r\nNicolas HOUNTO a développé, au cours de ses 20 années d’expérience de direction générale au sein d’entreprises européennes parmi lesquelles le leader européen des solutions spécialisées de gestion d’entreprises, des compétences solides de management d’entreprise, de recentrage stratégique et de développement des ventes.\r\nDepuis 2009 il se tourne vers l’appui aux entrepreneurs à haut potentiel dans le cadre d’Africangels dont il est co-fondateur et ses activités de conseil en développement des PME en Afrique sub-saharienne.\r\nIl participe notamment à la mise en œuvre de deux programmes de compétitions de plans d’affaires en Côte d’Ivoire dans le cadre du PEJEDEC (Programme Emploi Jeunes et Entreprenariat), et à l’accompagnement de plus de 80 entrepreneurs à forts potentiels en qualité de coach ou de mentor.\r\nEn 2014, il élabore pour la Banque Mondiale un concept innovant d’appui à l’entreprenariat des\r\njeunes à coût partagé au Togo, ce qui l’amènera quelques mois plus tard à conduire au Bénin, un\r\nprogramme financé par l’Institution dans le cadre du Projet de Compétitivité et de Croissance\r\nIntégrée (PCCI) durant 3 années, comprenant des programmes de formation à l’élaboration de plans d’affaires, de gestion d’entreprise et de coaching thématique pour le renforcement de capacité des entrepreneurs. Programme qui concerna 2675 candidats, et qui lui permis d’accompagner 130 entrepreneurs à lever plus de 4 000 000 € de financement.', 15, 2, 1, 1),
(100244, 'Aurélien ', 'DUVAL DELORT', 'Mr', '', '3', 'fr', '', '', 'aurelien.duvaldelort@orange.com', 'Bizao ', 'Aurélien is Founder and CEO of Bizao, a new Fintech startup helping companies partner with African mobile operators to access payment services (Mobile money & Carrier Billing). Bizao provides a very simple experience with one contract, one integration and one financial flow. Bizao has been accelerated at Orange Fab and has been recently launched across Orange footprint, more info on www.bizao.com\r\n\r\nAurélien has a MsC in Management from ESSEC Business School in Paris. He spent 7 years in management consulting in France and New York, USA before joining Orange in 2011, where he joined the Innovation division. Following several international digital projects, he joined the Middle-East & Africa team and launched the Orange Open API program to create a large ecosystem of partners using Orange APIs. Seeing how difficult it was for companies to partner with Orange, Aurélien identified the opportunity to build a pan-african, multi-operator platform prodiving a one-stop-shop for local and international companies: Bizao.\r\n\r\nAurélien has grown a passion for Africa region, meeting extraordinary people with great ideas and very innovative projects. He loves African music, kitesurfing in various regions of the world and mountaineering in the Alpes.', 8, 2, 1, 1),
(100245, 'Samia', 'ZAYANI', 'Mme', '', '3', 'tn', '', '', 'samia.zayani@dynamiqueeau.net ', 'Water Dynamic Organisation', 'CEO& Founder of Water Dynamic Organisation a multistakeholders platform in Tunisia for managing complexity in water Governance and water preservation, Samia ZAYANI  is a Telecoms & computer science engineer ( 2005)  and obtained a diploma of International affairs engineering in innovation and technologies from Mines-Telecom Business School Institute, Paris. In September 2014 , she published a professional thesis  “Inclusive Business Model Convergence : Challenges and Opportunities for Africa Development” . She is leading the Smart Water reflexion in Tunisia.', 8, 2, 1, 1),
(100246, 'Moez ', 'MAAREF', 'Mr', '', '3', 'tn', '', '', 'moez.maaref@ati.tn ', 'Tunisian Internet Agency', 'Moez MAAREF Was chairman of the Board of Directors of the Management Company of the Sfax Technopole since August 2017 , Mr. Maaref joined the office of the Minister of Communication Technologies and Digital Economy in 2016 as advisor for the implementation of implementation of the \"Tunisia 2020\" National Strategic Plan, having hitherto made a career in France (IBM, Areva, BNP Paribas, Société Générale Natixis) and in Luxembourg (Euroclear, management of stock market transactions).\r\n', 8, 2, 1, 1),
(100247, 'Mosbah ', 'HELALI', 'Mr', '', '3', 'tn', '', '', 'w.berrabah@sonede.com.tn', 'SONEDE', 'Mosbah Helali was born in 1965 in Sbeitla, governate of Kasserine, Tunisia. He holds a baccalauréat in mathematical sciences and an engineering degree in hydraulic and rural planning from the National Agronomy Institute of Tunisia. He also has a specialist degree in managing water for development from the National School for Rural Engineering of Water and Forests (ENGREF) in France.\r\nHe is currently the CEO of SONEDE, the National Society for the Use and Distribution of Water, which serves 3 million people and has 53,000 km of pipeline, 14 desalination stations, 12 surface water treatment plants and 4000 hydraulic projects. He is concurrently the President of the board of directors of SONEDE-International.\r\nMr. Helali began his career as a global engineering consultant before joining SONEDE in 1992 as Project Manager. At SONEDE, he worked his way up to Head of Division for Hydraulic Studies in North-West Tunisia in 1996, then Territorial Director for the North and Greater Tunis Studies in 2007, and then to Central Director of Studies in 2013 before becoming its CEO. At the start of 2016, Mr. Helali additionally became the CEO of the ELKANOUET society (the National Society for the Manufacture of Large Diameter Pipes and Pre-stressed Concrete Special Pieces).', 8, 2, 1, 1),
(100248, 'Alexander ', 'SAMARIN', 'Dr', '', '89', 'ch', '', '', 'alexander@samarin.com', 'SAMARIN.BIZ', 'Alexander Samarin wrote his first software program in the year 1973. He obtained a PhD (in computer graphics) in the year 1986. He has worked for a variety of international clients in Switzerland, UK, France, Australia and Africa (African Development Bank). He specialises as an architect, practitioner and methodologist for digital transformation of business and IT. In October 2009 he published a book “Improving enterprise business process management systems”. Since the year 2013, he, primarily, works in Digital Government, Digital Healthcare, Smart Cities, Smart Building and Homes, IoT and other systems domains.', 2, 2, 1, 1),
(100249, 'Mourad ', 'MELLITI', 'Mr', '', '30', 'tn', '', '', 'mourad@ati.tn', 'ATI', 'PhD, General Engineer Head of TIA’s Innovation Center where he is developing many research interests including Bigdata, SmartCities, Internet of Things and leads the company’s Innovation Program. He also became the MPA and the Technical Officer for DOA Servers in TUNISIA.', 22, 2, 1, 1),
(100250, 'Borhene ', 'DHAOUADI       ', 'Mr', '', '89', 'tn', '', '', 'borhene@bizertesmartcity.com', 'Bizerte Smart City', 'Borhene Dhaouadi, was born on 1 March 1980 in Bizerte, Tunisia. He is a Franco-Tunisian architect / urban planner, former Project Manager within the COPLAN Ingénierie Group, then in Marseille Architecture Partners and Manager of the DTA Group - Multidisciplinary Research Department since 2009. He is also president of the association Bizerte 2050 since 2011. After a Professional Diploma in Marine Carpentry and Architecture studies at the National School of Architecture of Marseille Luminy and then a Professional Master in Real Estate and Urban Policies to the Marseille Business School (Euromed), he joined in 2008, COPLAN Engineering Group through its subsidiary RTA and in 2009, they created the DTA Groupement in Tunisia with Renaud and Bernard Tarrazi, in which he becomes in a year Managing partner. He returned to the community after five years as treasurer at the Student Office of the National School of Architecture in Marseille (BDE) through the foundation in 2011 of the Association Bizerte 2050, which he is the President of. Since 2012, he has organized and led thematic workshops on the inclusive development of Northern Tunisia through strategic studies related to regional planning and the planning of economic infrastructures and modern transport in the north of the country on the principles of pooling of equipment and services, in partnership with the North East Chamber of Commerce (CCINE). In 2017, he launched the \"Bizerte Smart City\" Program with partners in institutional, legislative, professional and academic circles under the aegis of an Organizing Committee entitled: \"Bizerte Sustainable City\" of which he is the president. Under the direction of Borhene Dhaouadi, the Bizerte Smart City Program is moving forward since its launch in April 2017 with great steps to create in Bizerte an Ecosystem specializing in Smart Cities and Renewable Energies Unique of its kind in Tunisia and Africa through a 30-year city transformation program. The administrative and legal mechanisms associated with this approach are being studied by Borhene and its partners and will be part of a strategic document entitled \"Bizerte Smart City 2050\" which will be elaborated in consultation with the new municipal team after the Tunisian municipal elections scheduled for May 2018. The month of April 2018, Borhene prepared the launch of a National program entitled / Tunisian Smart Cities with the objective of making Tunisia the largest \"Smart City\" laboratory in Africa.', 2, 2, 1, 1),
(100251, 'Walid  ', 'BELLAGHA', 'Mr', '', '30', 'tn', '', '', 'walid.bellagha@endeavor.org', 'Endeavor Tunisia', 'Walid Bellagha is the Managing Director of Endeavor Tunisia. Before that he worked for 15 years in business development and marketing, primarily in consumer goods with Unilever, Danone and WhiteWave Foods in Tunisia and USA. Walid is also founding member and president of the Tunisian chapter of TAYP (Tunisian American Young Professionals)\r\n\r\n', 18, 2, 1, 1),
