(100309, 'Walid Sultan', 'MIDANI', 'Mr', '', '3', 'tn', '', '', 'wsmidani@gmail.com', 'DigitalMania', 'Walid Sultan MIDANI, CEO and Founder DigitalMania,Co-Director and Founder The Founders Institute - Tunisia\r\nFan of IT and a bit geeky, Walid graduated on July 2008 from ESPRIT-Tunisia as an IT Engineer. \r\nPioneer in Tunisia in the video games industry he also dedicates some of his time to NGOs that fight for freedom of speech.\r\n\r\nIn 2004: He landed in the video game ecosystem as a professional by co-founding his first startup Tunisiagames that organized the \"Electonic Sports Tunisian Cup\" from 2005 to 2009. He also took part in the organization board of the \"Electonic Sports World Cup - ESWC\" in Paris 2005 to 2007 and in California in 2008.\r\n\r\nIn 2011: He launched the first video game studio in Tunisia: DigitalMania.\r\nHe is now leading DigitalMania\'s team composed by 20+ people and he still takes part in the production process.\r\nIn 7 years, DigitalMania already released 125+ games on Web, Mobile, PC, and VR platforms. \r\n\r\nIn 2015: and as co-director of the Founder Institute in Tunisia, I started helping other entrepreneurs setting up their startups and raising funds. \r\n\r\nIn 2018: Launched the first worldwide game in VR for team building: www.theinfiniteloop.net\r\n\r\nIn 2019: His plans are to launch The Warshmallows : A cross-media experience that will mix a massive multiplayer game and a TV show.\r\n\r\nNote that Walid is still involved in citizen movements that fight for important causes in Tunisia and in Africa, like releasing the cannabis smokers from jail and upgrading outdated laws. \r\n', 8, 2, 1, 1),
