(100490, 'Carl ', 'Rodrigues', 'Mr', 'jurys', '', 'gb', '', '', '', '', 'With a focus on sales and strategy, Carl has spent over 20 years building and championing data-driven startups. He pioneered and grew the community at the Open Data Institute founded by World Wide Web inventor Sir Tim Berners-Lee. He is a Startups Mentor and Founder of Joining the Dots, a global online Scaleups network. He was instrumental in enabling the sale of streaming media provider Servecast to Level 3 Communications for $45m in July 2007, as head of their corporate business. In 2018 he won a Trusted IoT Alliance award for a blockchain powered project gathering realtime data from cars to improve road congestion and safety with his client Streamr and Bosch. He currently advises SageCity a blockchain startup and scouts for Scaleups for CoVentured who match corporates and Scaleups for innovation programmes. He has spoken internationally on emerging technologies, data and smart cities.\r\n\r\nHe is passionate about connecting people and organisations, supporting the use of technology for good, investing in startups and cryptocurrencies and empowering others to raise investment via crowdfunding. He is also an executive and career coach and has a degree in Classics from Kingâ€™s College Cambridge. \r\n', 0, 2, 0, 1);
