(100211, 'Patrick', 'KEDZIORA', 'Mr', '', '3', 'us', '', '', 'patrick@boilingice.com', 'Kedzoh', 'I am deeply passionate about building businesses that have a huge impact on the world and connecting with clients, partners, investors, and employees and infusing them with my passion. If you do that, the revenues and profits will simply follow.\r\n\r\nI am an entrepreneur, founder, and part of the founding team of three companies.\r\n\r\nCurrently, I am building the world\'s dominant learning portal in the field of digital dentistry - KedzohDental.com.\r\n\r\nAmongst my achievements, I have won highly coveted spots in Startup Chile, Startup Brazil, and French TechTicket.\r\n\r\nI have been the CFO and COO of public and private companies. I have done deals - both small and large - from a few million to a few billion. With former clients like KKR (the leading private equity firm) and T. Boone Pickens (a major Texas oilman and investor), I\'ve been to the front lines and back.\r\n\r\nWhether doing business in the U.S. or internationally, I\'m equally at ease in the boardroom as I am on the shop floor. And, I speak native English and native French and fluent Spanish and Portuguese. I also have dual US and French nationality and am able to work in both the US and the EU; but if you\'re wondering: I\'m a New Yorker at heart.\r\n\r\nI received my M.B.A. in Finance from the Stern School of Business at New York University and a double B.A. in both Economics and Political Science from New York University.\r\n\r\nMy passion is growing businesses and all things mobile and global ... as mobile is indeed transforming the world we live in. \"You\'re not global if you\'re not mobile\"™', 8, 2, 1, 1),
(100209, 'Tomi', 'DAVIES', 'Mr', '', '3', 'ng', '', '+447944151804', 'td@tvcng.com', 'TechnoVision - ABAN', 'Harry Tomi Davies (TD) is an IT systems analyst turned advisor, public speaker and angel investor with 20+ years of accomplishments leading implementation of innovative technology-led transformation initiatives within the oil & gas, retail, telecommunications, technology and hospitality industries. He has outstanding experience building large-scale, national and region-wide technology enabled systems projects in the US, Europe and Africa gained from a variety of executive leadership roles with influential global brands including Ernst & Young, Marks & Spencer, Elf Aquitaine, Sapient and the One Laptop Per Child project.\r\n\r\nHe is a strong strategic planner, problem solver and project manager who consistently delivers results while contributing with excellence. TD has been regularly recognised for success in building teams and developing cost-effective approaches that streamline corporate processes to enhance operational performance. HIs experiences in Africa using a goal-oriented approach to project planning and execution that consistently delivered effective results inspired his 2014 book “The African Project Manager”.\r\n\r\nTD is \"Collaborator-in-Chief\" of technology services company TechnoVision which advises clients on technology-led transformation and early stage entrepreneurship in Africa. He is co-founder of the Lagos Angel Network (LAN), President of the African Business Angel Network (ABAN) and board member at MBO Capital (Private Equity) and TextNigeria (Telecoms).\r\n\r\nAs a thought leader and entrepreneur with start-up expertise gained from building a growing portfolio of tech-enabled early stage businesses originating from Africa, his personal goal is to help \"drive the development of Africa through entrepreneurship that is creating social and economic value using technology”.\r\n\r\n', 7, 2, 1, 1),
(100212, 'Niyi', 'AKINMOLAYAN', 'Mr', '', '110', 'ng', '', '', '	manuyie@gmail.com', 'Anthill Studios', 'Niyi Akinmolayan was born in Lagos, Nigeria. His first feature was a sci-fi movie Kajola in 2009. He has since gone to make more critically acclaimed features and documentaries.\r\nHe also runs Nigeria\'s biggest post production studio for film and television; ANTHILL studios.', 25, 2, 1, 1),
(100213, ' Bankole', 'OLORUNTOBA', 'Mr', '', '110', 'ng', '', '', 'bankole@nine.org.ng', 'Network of Incubators and Innovators in Nigeria (NINe)', 'Currently managing enspire Business Incubator, a technology focused business incubation centre under the Abuja Technology Village. I re-designed and set up the existing platform with its re-purposed areas of focus. Developing and Managing of the Abuja Tech Ecosystem to serve as a resource pool for the enspire Incubator. An expert on the Business Model Canvas deployment for Start ups. Incubation Management and Advisory, Strength in the identification and Building of strategic work partners. Creator of Abuja Techies Meet-ups (Monthly). I have a clear understanding of the Start-ups and Entrepreneurship sector in Nigeria/West Africa.\r\n\r\nCreator of Abuja Techie Meet-up (A monthly gathering of Abuja Tech free lance and start up ecosystem). Co-Founded Nigerian Incubators and Innovators Network, 3rd Sector Support Africa, StartupArewa and SocialGood Nigeria/Abuja Social GoodHub .\r\n\r\nIn addition, in 2014, I set up and remotely directed the Marketing and Sales Unit of WE 106.3FM Abuja. Business Development, Corporate Brand positioning, Sales, Sponsorship and Partnership coordination.\r\n\r\nI co-managed the set up process of the Osun State Tourism Industrial Programme (OTOURS) and the built a Media/PR strategy for the effective public communication of the programme. And I was also involved with the soft re-positioning of the Osun State Youth Employment Scheme (OYES) which include Developing quick win strategies, Training of OYES Cadets\r\n\r\nAlso I consulted for the Nigerian Film and Video Censors’ Board in the building of a Digital Technology Film Distribution platform as a business, social and industry development platform.\r\n\r\nA member of the Presidential Council on Technology, Innovation and Creativity. \r\n\r\nInnovation Mgt and commercialization advisor, Incubation Program design advisory. Venture Builder.', 15, 2, 1, 1),
(100214, 'Rudy', 'CASBI', 'Mr', '', '97', 'fr', '', '', 'rudy.casbi@yahoo.fr', 'CIO Mag', 'Journaliste à Afrique Agriculture, Les Afriques Finance Edition, radio shalom\r\n', 26, 2, 1, 1),
(100215, 'Selma ', 'ELLOUMI REKIK', 'Mme', '', '41', 'tn', '', '', 'presse@tourisme.gov.tn', 'Ministère du Tourisme et de l’Artisanat', 'Selma Elloumi Rekik, ministre  du Tourisme et de l’Artisanat au sein du gouvernement d’union nationale, a été députée de NidaaTounes. Femme d\'affaires, elle rejoint NidaaTounes avec son frère Faouzi Elloumi (le PDG de Cofat) dès sa création. Elle devient par la suite membre du comité exécutif du parti.\r\n\r\nAprès son diplôme de management à l’Institut supérieur de gestion de Tunis, elle intègre l’entreprise familiale, le groupe Elloumi. \r\n\r\nElle s’intéresse vite à l’agroalimentaire et devient la patronne de l’entreprise agroalimentaire Stifen. Elle a développé en 20 ans une grande activité agricole et agroalimentaire dans la région du Cap Bon, essentiellement orientée vers l’exportation.\r\n\r\n', 20, 2, 1, 1),
(100216, 'Thibault', 'VERBIEST', 'Mr', '', '93', 'be', '', '', 'VERBIEST@dsavocats.com', 'DS Avocats', 'An attorney in Paris and Brussels since 1993, Thibault Verbiest founded Ulys, a law firm dedicated to new technologies. He was notably able to develop a renowned expertise in legislation pertaining to payments and e-money, gaming and other regulated online activities.\r\n\r\nBetween 2000 and 2004, he was the chairman of I’Observatoire des droits de I’intemet, an organisation tasked with advising the Belgian federal government on its policymaking approach towards the internet.  In 2013, he founded two fintechs, including Payservices. Until 2015, he was also partner of investment bank Largillière Finance, which specializes in Fintech M&A.\r\nln 2015,  he joined the law firm de Gaulle Fleurance as a partner to create the fintech, blockchain and cryptocurrency practice, which has, since then earned a solid reputation before moving to DS Avocats in September 2017 to create the first Pole entirely dedicated to Fintech, Digital Banking and Crypto-finance.\r\nHe is also the co-author of several books, including the first book on blockchain in French and the seminal piece ‘Fintech et Droit”. He regularly contributes to the public debate on blockchain, and is a speaker at fintech-blockchain focused events. He is a legal advisor for a number of ICO’s, exchanges and crypto funds in Europe. He also acts as expert with the European Blockchain Observatory and Forum and with the World Bank.', 27, 2, 1, 1),
(100220, 'Celine ', 'DUROS', 'Mme', '', '30', 'gh', '', '', 'celine@meltwater.org', 'MEST Africa', 'A Meltwater sales veteran, Celine joined MEST full time after leading intensive sales training for EITs at MEST as a Meltwater Sales Fellow. Celine is originally from France and joined the Meltwater sales team in Paris following her MIB from Grenoble Ecole de Management in France. She now leads operations for MEST Accra.', 0, 0, 0, 1);

